        "text": "παλιγγενεσία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and of the perfected theocracy in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αἰὼν μέλλων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Comp. on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "impersonal",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " view (Paulus, Baumgarten-Crusius), according to which the meaning is said to be: till the establishment of the kingdom shall be brought about, is an evasion opposed to the context. Completely without foundation, moreover, Schenkel says that the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "adoption of the Gentiles",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " into the divine covenant is the fulfilment of the Old Testament Passover.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 22:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " f. According to Luke, Jesus, after He had spoken quite at the beginning of the meal the words, ",
        "children": []
      },
